87
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,700
The message you sent me.

88
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:30,680
(Let's get divorced.
You can keep Yangao.)

89
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:32,790
You said you didn't want
to take care of Yan anymore.

90
00:08:33,170 --> 00:08:35,830
If this goes to arbitration,
how do you think the court will rule?

91
00:08:37,570 --> 00:08:38,960
There's a lawyer's office next door.

92
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,360
Feel free to get some legal advice.

93
00:08:40,440 --> 00:08:41,320
Cui Ye.

94
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,200
You scoundrel!

95
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,270
When did I ever send you that message?

96
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,870
Answer me!

97
00:09:05,870 --> 00:09:06,870
After you found out

98
00:09:07,910 --> 00:09:09,270
Yan was sick.

99
00:09:13,180 --> 00:09:15,100
(Cui Yangao, Motor Neurone Disease)

100
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:23,150
You think you're better than me?

101
00:09:23,150 --> 00:09:25,150
That you could give Yan a better life?

102
00:09:25,150 --> 00:09:26,200
You misjudged me

103
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,790
and you misjudged yourself.

104
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,510
Now I can afford to treat Yan,

105
00:09:29,510 --> 00:09:30,870
can you?

106
00:09:52,390 --> 00:09:53,630
Think about it.

107
00:09:54,870 --> 00:09:55,720
If you want a divorce,

108
00:09:57,240 --> 00:09:58,360
I'll go along with it.

109
00:09:58,790 --> 00:10:00,750
If not, come with me to Hong Kong, China

110
00:10:01,390 --> 00:10:02,790
and get Yan treated.

111
00:10:16,900 --> 00:10:17,750
Yuck!

112
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:19,150
This is still raw!

113
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:26,630
For Yan,

114
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:28,870
I'd do anything.

115
00:10:51,510 --> 00:10:52,630
You're back.

116
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:54,120
I'm going to pick up Yan.

117
00:10:58,750 --> 00:10:59,590
Mom.

118
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:02,390
Where's that old double blanket?

119
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:03,870
In the cupboard.

120
00:11:03,870 --> 00:11:05,120
You don't even use it.

121
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,360
Why are you asking?

122
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:09,720
Shuhua is coming back
to stay for a few days.

123
00:11:12,390 --> 00:11:13,790
She's coming back?

124
00:11:13,790 --> 00:11:14,900
You're not getting divorced?

125
00:11:18,270 --> 00:11:19,790
You talked to her?

126
00:11:22,630 --> 00:11:24,120
That's wonderful!

127
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,870
What did she say?

128
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,000
She said

129
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:30,270
she wants us to continue being a family.

130
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:32,000
Really?

131
00:11:32,390 --> 00:11:34,000
That's great!

132
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,510
I'll tell Yan when I see him.

133
00:11:35,510 --> 00:11:37,150
He'll be over the moon!

134
00:11:38,630 --> 00:11:39,630
You should get going.

135
00:11:39,820 --> 00:11:40,690
All right.

136
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,120
I'm going to pick up Yan now.

137
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:44,240
This is wonderful!

138
00:11:59,000 --> 00:11:59,870
Come in.

139
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:03,910
Shuhua?

140
00:12:04,510 --> 00:12:05,720
You're here early.

141
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,750
Is something the matter?

142
00:12:07,630 --> 00:12:08,630
Ms. Wu,

143
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:10,150
I'd like

144
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:12,150
to drop out.

145
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,480
What about your oral lessons?

146
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:16,150
I won't need them anymore.

147
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:23,600
Captain.

148
00:12:26,390 --> 00:12:27,630
You came in person.

149
00:12:36,510 --> 00:12:37,480
It's a pity.

150
00:12:38,150 --> 00:12:39,510
Looks like the game is off.

151
00:13:03,110 --> 00:13:04,390
Aren't you going to question me?

152
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,750
I was going to ask.

153
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:11,360
Captain Cui.

154
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,000
I think you'd do better

155
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:17,390
than me in business.

156
00:13:19,030 --> 00:13:20,630
You're calm.

157
00:13:23,630 --> 00:13:25,120
Are you sure about that?

158
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:31,000
Tech department says

159
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,480
(Public Security)
the ship was cleaned.

160
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,600
No fingerprints left behind.

161
00:13:33,610 --> 00:13:35,150
They're analyzing the blood samples now.

162
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:50,120
Did Wang Hongyu say anything?

163
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:54,630
Nothing at all?

164
00:13:57,390 --> 00:13:58,630
I didn't ask him anything.

165
00:13:59,210 --> 00:14:00,990
Even if I had,
he wouldn't have said a word.

166
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,630
I think he was set up.

167
00:14:05,870 --> 00:14:07,480
He's probably as confused as I am.

168
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:10,120
We've been over all the details

169
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,390
too many times now.

170
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:14,120
So many theories.

171
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,120
Each one feels like a lead,

172
00:14:16,870 --> 00:14:18,390
but none of them connect.

173
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,980
We don't even know
which direction to go in anymore.

174
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,870
If Qin Xiaoming wasn't
one of the five robbers,

175
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,510
then who was the fifth one?

176
00:14:35,630 --> 00:14:37,270
At the time of the crime,

177
00:14:37,270 --> 00:14:39,390
they chose someone to be the decoy.

178
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:42,030
Why him?

179
00:14:44,390 --> 00:14:45,480
Did this person

180
00:14:46,390 --> 00:14:49,000
do it to protect someone?

181
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:51,150
Who was he protecting?

182
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,240
The one who wet his pants.

183
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:09,420
(The guy who wet his pants,
Qin Xiaoming)

184
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:23,340
(The guy who wet his pants)

185
00:15:29,270 --> 00:15:30,110
Captain,

186
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,390
the prosecutor's review is complete.

187
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,390
They said the body
will be processed today.

188
00:15:45,300 --> 00:15:49,180
(Lanshui City Credit Union,
Criminal No. 1, shot dead)

189
00:16:56,630 --> 00:16:57,470
Captain!

190
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,270
What do you think that rat was
to the other rat?

191
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,000
Its mother?

192
00:17:09,880 --> 00:17:11,270
Its wife? Child?

193
00:17:12,110 --> 00:17:13,030
Its brother?

194
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:17,000
Who would you risk your life for?

195
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:19,790
Sun.

196
00:17:19,790 --> 00:17:21,750
We've got the DNA results

197
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:24,120
from the blood samples taken
from the fishing boat's rope.

198
00:17:24,350 --> 00:17:26,030
After analyzing the genetic markers,

199
00:17:26,350 --> 00:17:28,830
we found that the suspect
and the deceased suspect

200
00:17:28,830 --> 00:17:30,310
were biological brothers.

201
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:33,310
Biological brothers.

202
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,070
We can't even confirm
the deceased's identity.

203
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:39,960
What's the use of knowing
they're brothers?

204
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:57,270
I have an idea.

205
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:00,000
Run it through Chief Zhao first.

206
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:04,080
Come on!

207
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:15,260
(Youyi Department Store)

208
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:30,070
I'm off, Li.

209
00:18:30,510 --> 00:18:31,720
See you, Chen.

210
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,750
Have a piece of melon.

211
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:37,750
Stop fussing with the schedule.
I'm in no mood to eat.

212
