281
00:24:57,590 --> 00:24:58,750
Plans?

282
00:24:59,960 --> 00:25:01,270
Like,

283
00:25:01,590 --> 00:25:03,270
what kind of life

284
00:25:03,270 --> 00:25:05,510
do you want to have in ten years?

285
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:08,000
Ten years from now?

286
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,200
Who knows what'll happen in ten years?

287
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:13,680
Right now,

288
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,590
I just hope we can deliver

289
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:17,000
this batch of orders on time.

290
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:19,440
That way, the factory can keep running.

291
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:21,510
Keep running for good.

292
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:24,000
You care a lot about the factory.

293
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:27,270
I grew up there with my mom.

294
00:25:27,790 --> 00:25:30,240
When I was a kid and had
to write essays about "My Family,"

295
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,960
I wrote about the factory.

296
00:25:33,160 --> 00:25:34,030
In the summer,

297
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:36,510
the whole factory would
watch movies outdoor together.

298
00:25:36,830 --> 00:25:38,000
The movie stars
were fighting on the screen,

299
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,440
and we were having fun in the seats.

300
00:25:40,350 --> 00:25:42,790
In winter, we'd all cram
into the conference room

301
00:25:42,790 --> 00:25:44,750
to watch a tiny TV.
But it never felt crowded.

302
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:52,270
After my mom passed away,

303
00:25:52,510 --> 00:25:53,830
I took over her job.

304
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:57,270
Even though I'm the youngest one there,

305
00:25:58,270 --> 00:26:00,030
everyone still calls me Ms. Xia,

306
00:26:00,310 --> 00:26:01,550
like they used to call my mom.

307
00:26:07,130 --> 00:26:08,030
You're young,

308
00:26:08,030 --> 00:26:09,200
but you rank pretty high, huh?

309
00:26:09,510 --> 00:26:10,350
Ms. Xia.

310
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,000
You can't call me that!
You make me sound old!

311
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:19,560
Anything else?

312
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,440
Wellâ€¦

313
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:29,030
There's my dad.

314
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:33,750
You're close with your dad?

315
00:26:35,830 --> 00:26:38,750
I used to wish
he'd disappear from my life forever.

316
00:26:46,070 --> 00:26:47,550
Why are you looking at me like that?

317
00:26:47,550 --> 00:26:49,310
You don't know
what kind of person he was.

318
00:26:53,270 --> 00:26:54,920
But he's better now.

319
00:26:57,270 --> 00:26:58,510
I hope things

320
00:26:58,920 --> 00:27:00,680
can just stay good like this.

321
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:02,590
That would be nice.

322
00:27:07,550 --> 00:27:08,550
This is my home.

323
00:27:15,830 --> 00:27:16,920
Wait here.

324
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,510
What's this for?

325
00:27:31,510 --> 00:27:32,590
It's for your dad.

326
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:34,200
He won't accept this.

327
00:27:35,410 --> 00:27:37,270
Consider it my way
of showing respect to him.

328
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:14,200
You should head inside.

329
00:28:16,510 --> 00:28:17,440
I'm off.

330
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,480
Don't miss me.

331
00:29:07,310 --> 00:29:08,240
Xia Yu.

332
00:29:10,750 --> 00:29:11,920
Who's that boy?

333
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,070
Your new boyfriend?

334
00:29:13,790 --> 00:29:14,830
He bought this for you.

335
00:29:17,350 --> 00:29:19,340
(Lanshui Lucky Welfare Lottery)
He has good manners, at least.

336
00:29:19,410 --> 00:29:20,750
You bought lottery tickets again?

337
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:24,270
This is a welfare lottery.

338
00:29:24,590 --> 00:29:25,750
It's not gambling.

339
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:35,480
Ladies and gentlemen,

340
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:37,750
thank you for tuning in
to tonight's "Life On the Line."

341
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:39,510
I'm Xinwen.

342
00:29:39,790 --> 00:29:42,750
We're joined
by a very special guest tonight.

343
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:45,240
Captain Cui Wei
of the City Criminal Police Division.

344
00:29:45,550 --> 00:29:46,720
Hello, Captain Cui.

345
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,000
Hello.

346
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,310
I'm sure you must be a fan

347
00:29:50,310 --> 00:29:52,480
of Romance of the Three Kingdoms.

348
00:29:53,750 --> 00:29:55,030
It's all right.

349
00:29:55,030 --> 00:29:57,550
Let me guess
which event's your favorite.

350
00:29:58,030 --> 00:29:59,420
The Oath of the Peach Garden?

351
00:29:59,420 --> 00:30:00,660
(Lanshui City Radio)

352
00:30:00,660 --> 00:30:01,750
Gathering of the Heroes?

353
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:03,750
I bet you like

354
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:06,270
the Three Visits
to the Thatched Cottage.

355
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:09,000
Why's that?

356
00:30:09,790 --> 00:30:11,550
Because this is the third time

357
00:30:11,550 --> 00:30:13,270
we've invited you onto the show.

358
00:30:14,620 --> 00:30:15,480
I see.

359
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,510
Just kidding.

360
00:30:16,510 --> 00:30:17,590
It's an honor

361
00:30:17,590 --> 00:30:19,000
to have you here.

362
00:30:19,310 --> 00:30:20,160
So, Captain Cui,

363
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:22,750
what would you like to share
with our listeners tonight?

364
00:30:23,070 --> 00:30:24,790
Good evening, everyone.

365
00:30:25,270 --> 00:30:27,200
I'd like to talk about

366
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:29,070
the handling

367
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:30,790
of criminal suspects.

368
00:30:31,060 --> 00:30:31,900
Sir,

369
00:30:31,910 --> 00:30:34,550
are you tuning in to 95.4 FM?

370
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,590
Why does the show sound different today?

371
00:30:37,590 --> 00:30:39,550
Do I look like their boss?

372
00:30:39,550 --> 00:30:41,030
We're giving the public

373
00:30:41,030 --> 00:30:42,590
an overview of how

374
00:30:42,590 --> 00:30:44,270
our police department handles

375
00:30:44,510 --> 00:30:46,000
these kinds of cases.

376
00:30:46,510 --> 00:30:48,440
That was a hard pivot.

377
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:03,550
It looks like we already have
a caller on the line.

378
00:31:03,550 --> 00:31:05,310
Let's take this call together.

379
00:31:06,550 --> 00:31:07,480
Officer,

380
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:08,720
I have a question.

381
00:31:09,070 --> 00:31:11,240
If you kill a criminal

382
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:12,790
in the line of duty,

383
00:31:12,790 --> 00:31:14,500
what do you do with the body?

384
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:20,680
First, we verify the identity
of the deceased criminal

385
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:22,310
and notify their family.

386
00:31:22,310 --> 00:31:24,310
If we can't confirm the identity

387
00:31:24,590 --> 00:31:27,200
or no family members come forward,

388
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:31,440
we transfer the body to a relevant hospital
or research institute.

389
00:31:31,450 --> 00:31:33,400
If no one claims the body
after a certain period,

390
00:31:33,410 --> 00:31:36,270
we hand it over to
the local civil affairs department.

391
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:38,270
(Lanshui City Radio)
Captain Cui, I have a question.

392
00:31:38,550 --> 00:31:40,030
What does

393
00:31:40,030 --> 00:31:42,270
the civil affairs department do next?

394
00:31:42,450 --> 00:31:44,810
To my understanding,
they will follow the standard procedure

395
00:31:44,820 --> 00:31:46,000
and cremate the body.

396
00:31:46,080 --> 00:31:46,920
Afterward,

397
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:49,440
the ashes will be stored
at a funeral home for a period of time.

398
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,800
If no one claims the remains,

399
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:52,990
the funeral home will handle them
at their discretion.

400
00:31:54,270 --> 00:31:57,240
We'd like to remind our listeners

401
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,510
to follow the law.

402
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:00,920
Otherwise, not only will you

403
00:32:00,920 --> 00:32:02,960
face legal consequences,

404
00:32:02,960 --> 00:32:03,850
but you may also

405
00:32:03,850 --> 00:32:05,350
never find peace, even in death.

406
00:32:10,590 --> 00:32:11,830
That'll hit him where it hurts.

407
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:21,510
Let's take the next caller.

408
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,160
Hello, caller. You're on the air.

409
00:32:24,960 --> 00:32:26,750
Hello, Xinwen.

410
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:28,270
I have some thoughts

411
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:29,550
about what the officer said.

412
00:32:29,830 --> 00:32:31,200
Criminals are a threat to society

413
00:32:31,350 --> 00:32:32,680
when they're alive.

414
00:32:32,680 --> 00:32:34,160
They're just a waste of resources.

415
00:32:34,510 --> 00:32:36,480
Why should they get a proper burial?

416
00:32:36,610 --> 00:32:38,030
Why even bother keeping their ashes?

417
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:39,960
The state shouldn't waste money on that!

418
00:32:40,590 --> 00:32:42,310
What nonsense are they spouting?

419
00:32:56,900 --> 00:32:59,860
(Lanshui City Radio)

420
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:03,720
Let's take the next caller.

421
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,310
Hello.

422
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:12,960
Hello?

423
00:33:27,200 --> 00:33:28,750
Good evening, caller.

424
00:33:28,800 --> 00:33:30,000
Do you have a question for me?

425
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:32,000
I can answer it for you.

426
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:38,830
I was just gathering my thoughts.

427
00:33:40,270 --> 00:33:41,550
Some callers may have

428
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:43,510
their own views,

429
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:46,270
but this policy reflects

430
00:33:46,830 --> 00:33:48,440
the state's humanity

431
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:51,030
and respect for every citizen.

432
00:33:55,550 --> 00:33:58,590
This caller sounds like
a government official.

433
00:33:59,270 --> 00:34:02,830
Thank you for supporting our work.

434
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:06,000
You make a fair point. Thank you.

435
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:16,480
Sorry, we have another caller
ahead of you. Please hold.

436
00:34:22,620 --> 00:34:25,580
(Lanshui Station, Ticket Office)

437
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,670
This is a list of all the calls
we received tonight.

438
00:34:53,670 --> 00:34:55,400
We hope this will help you.

439
00:34:57,630 --> 00:34:58,760
Thank you.

440
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:01,440
Can you replay this for a few days?

441
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:02,550
Of course.

442
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:05,630
If more calls come in,
please keep a record for me.

443
00:35:05,630 --> 00:35:07,200
- All right.
- Thank you.

444
00:35:07,590 --> 00:35:08,590
I'll get back to work.

445
00:35:08,590 --> 00:35:09,430
All right.

446
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:14,880
Let's hope he hears it.

447
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:18,590
We're taking a risk here.

448
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,190
This really is a gamble.

449
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:24,960
Do we have another choice?

450
00:35:25,410 --> 00:35:26,670
Keep an eye on the funeral home.

451
00:35:27,030 --> 00:35:28,630
See if anyone suspicious shows up.

452
00:35:33,420 --> 00:35:36,620
(Lanshui-Dantong)

453
00:35:43,260 --> 00:35:49,460
(Passenger Train Schedule)

454
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,150
Captain.

455
00:36:08,550 --> 00:36:10,030
Any updates on your side?

456
00:36:10,030 --> 00:36:11,440
Nothing at all.

457
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:13,440
(Lanshui City Funeral Home)

458
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:14,800
I've already checked the register.

459
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:16,110
Stay sharp.

460
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:18,440
I'll have Ma take over for you in a bit.

461
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:19,690
I'll complete the mission, sir.

462
00:36:24,180 --> 00:36:28,020
(Lanshui City Funeral Home)

463
00:36:28,260 --> 00:36:31,500
(Liang's Cold Noodles)

464
00:36:44,190 --> 00:36:45,280
Anything else?

465
00:36:46,110 --> 00:36:47,070
No.

466
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:48,320
Thank you.

467
00:36:48,670 --> 00:36:49,510
You're welcome.

468
00:37:12,110 --> 00:37:12,950
Are you finished?

469
00:37:13,080 --> 00:37:14,480
Got any more of those cigarettes?

470
00:37:14,840 --> 00:37:15,920
(Xiuli Jiangshan)
These are mine.

471
00:37:16,110 --> 00:37:17,030
Only half a pack left.

472
00:37:17,030 --> 00:37:18,000
You can have it for free.

473
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:19,670
Thank you.

474
00:37:19,840 --> 00:37:20,880
Don't worry about it.

475
00:37:22,590 --> 00:37:24,710
Give me a Fengcheng Laojiao too.

476
00:37:27,190 --> 00:37:28,030
Here you go.

477
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:45,760
Here, have a cigarette.

478
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:46,760
It'll keep you awake.

479
00:37:48,030 --> 00:37:49,280
I'm sorry. I don't smoke.

480
00:37:52,760 --> 00:37:53,800
What's wrong?

481
00:37:54,150 --> 00:37:55,030
Nothing.

482
00:37:56,070 --> 00:37:57,710
No one here smiles.

483
00:37:58,190 --> 00:37:59,590
Seeing you smile

484
00:38:00,280 --> 00:38:01,710
feels a bit strange.

485
00:38:13,580 --> 00:38:16,060
(Complex)

486
00:38:25,400 --> 00:38:26,760
I got you what you wanted.

487
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:31,920
I'm heading back.

488
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:36,920
Take care.

489
00:39:20,590 --> 00:39:21,960
I think it's Dai.

490
00:39:22,760 --> 00:39:24,670
Dai delivers stuff for his father.

491
00:39:24,880 --> 00:39:26,800
His dad's not in great shape mentally.

492
00:39:26,920 --> 00:39:27,920
What does he deliver

493
00:39:27,930 --> 00:39:29,280
that needs him working this late?

494
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:31,480
Makeup supplies.

495
00:39:31,880 --> 00:39:32,760
Our line of work

496
00:39:33,030 --> 00:39:33,870
has no set schedules.

497
00:39:49,070 --> 00:39:51,400
What case are you working on?

498
00:39:51,710 --> 00:39:54,710
Are you looking for
a live man or a dead one?

499
00:39:58,230 --> 00:39:59,110
Officer,

500
00:39:59,110 --> 00:40:00,760
please don't mind me.

501
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:03,280
I don't get a lot of people to talk to,

502
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:06,480
working the night shift.

503
00:40:06,880 --> 00:40:07,720
I understand.
